    <title>Isosceles Triangle convert to Polygon, change Save file to re-Open file</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">In LibreOffice-3.5.1 Draw: Basic Shapes, Isosceles Triangle.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">Draw big triangle taking half of page, taking top half of page.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">This Triangle object selected, &gt; Convert &gt; To Polygon.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">&gt; Save in ODG file.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.5">Close.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.6">Open recent documents, re-open file.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.7">The polygon has changed position, now at bottom of page.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Probably related:</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">- no such problem for a triangle by Filled Polygon, 3 sided polygon.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">- with Isosceles Triangle converted to Polygon, [Points(F8)] On in Draw toolbar shows 5 edit points, but for triangle from Filled Polygon with 3 sides, only 3 points.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">Clearly not same type of Polygons, but should not cause the Save then ReLoad problem.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
